title: Chucky Goes Into Overdrive | Gelfand vs Ivanchuk | Candidates Tournament 2013. | Round 4
description:
#agadmator In Tuesday’s fourth round of the FIDE World Chess Candidates’ Tournament in London Magnus Carlsen of Norway caught Levon Aronian of Armenia in first place. Carlsen beat Alexander Grischuk of Russia in a Ruy Lopez Berlin, while Aronian was held to a draw by Peter Svidler of Russia in a Queen’s Gambit Accepted. The two oldest participants, Boris Gelfand of Israel and Vassily Ivanchuk of Ukraine, drew a very interesting game that started with the rare Chigorin Defence. Teimour Radjabov of Azerbaijan and Vladimir Kramnik of Russia drew a Nimzo-Indian that was always more or less balanced. 

Read more here: http://london2013.fide.com/en/component/content/article/1-news-en/203-round-4-magnus-carlsen-catches-levon-aronian-in-first-place-at-fide-candidates

Check out all photos from Round 4 of the 2013 candidates tournament here http://london2013.fide.com/images/stories/gallery/Round%204%20London/index.html

Boris Gelfand vs Vassily Ivanchuk
World Championship Candidates (2013), London ENG, rd 4, Mar-19 
Queen's Gambit Declined: Chigorin Defense. Main Line (D07)

1. d4 d5 2. c4 Nc6 3. Nf3 Bg4 4. Nc3 e6 5. Bf4 Bf3 6. gf3 Bb4 7. e3 Nge7 8. Qc2 dc4 9. Bc4 Nd5 10. Bg3 h5 11. h3 Qd7 12. O-O-O O-O-O 13. Ne4 Kb8 14. Kb1 h4 15. Bh2 Bd6 16. f4 f5 17. Ng5 Na5 18.
